<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>BEWARE&gt;&gt;&gt;SCAM ARTIST</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?Cappadocias ForgottenOne">Cappadocias ForgottenOne</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 5:00 a.m. 9/12/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> BEWARE&gt;&gt;&gt;SCAM ARTIST<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>BEWARE ALL,

<P>Especially guilds that have members playing 'twinks'. Me and a couple of friends were scammed outta some valuable gear by a low lvl char claiming to be a guild members 2nd char.The story is long and the details are many. The Warning i give is simple. BE DAMNED SURE the person you are dealing with is who they are and if you are not certain, Make them log on as the person you know and have that person give you the name of their other character. We are currently thinking that the person involved is associated with the infamous Sheki and gang. The name of the mule con artist is Garodil. I pleaded with a GM to look up the account to determine the other characters on the account so that we might have some indication of the bastard behind the newbie mule. I was given the standard answer for misfortunes.Im sure Garodil will be destroyed as soon as the transfer of stolen goods is complete. Again, learn by others misfortunes and do not trust anyone until they can prove themselves.
<P>It is ashame to see these types of ppl in the world. May their souls rot in hell!
<BR>Cappadocias ForgottenOne
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
